The following snippet shows how to use a formatter in a template. The formatter below is
`ng:format="reverse"`, added as an attribute to an `<input>` tag.  

<pre>
Formatted:
<input type="text" name="data" value="angular" ng:format="reverse"/>
<br/>
</pre>

The following sample shows how to use a formatter in JavaScript:

<pre>
...
var userInputString = angular.formatter.json.format(modelValue);
...
</pre>


